title: Millburn High School football team suffers first defeat
text:
Millburn High School football team suffers first defeat October 10, 2015 Last updated: Saturday, October 10, 2015, 8:51 PM By Jim Connelly Print 
Evidence Njoku scored two touchdowns in the first half Oct. 10, the second coming on a kickoff return for a score with 51 seconds remaining before halftime to snap a 7-7 tie and spark visiting Cedar Grove High School to a 28-14 defeat of Millburn High School in the Super Essex Conference, Colonial Division opener for both squads. 
Millburn fell to 3-1. Cedar Grove is 4-1. 
The Millers' scores came on a pass from Peter Serruto to John Serruto with 1:02 left in the first half and on a Zack Weinstein touchdown run with four minutes remaining in the contest. 
See the Thursday, Oct. 15, 2015, print edition of The Item of Millburn and Short Hills for more details.
